                    "message": {
                        "text": "Reentrancy in Wallet.exchange(string,address,uint256) (../sb/Wallet_F.sol#526-558):\n\tExternal calls:\n\t- (success,data) = exchangeContract.call(abi.encodeWithSignature(isSupported(string),targetCurrency)) (../sb/Wallet_F.sol#535-537)\n\tState variables written after the call(s):\n\t- balances[msg.sender] -= amount (../sb/Wallet_F.sol#540)\n\tWallet.balances (../sb/Wallet_F.sol#431) can be used in cross function reentrancies:\n\t- Wallet.deposit() (../sb/Wallet_F.sol#482-486)\n\t- Wallet.exchange(string,address,uint256) (../sb/Wallet_F.sol#526-558)\n\t- Wallet.exchangeAUTH(string,address,address,uint256) (../sb/Wallet_F.sol#628-666)\n\t- Wallet.externalTransfer(uint256,address) (../sb/Wallet_F.sol#508-518)\n\t- Wallet.externalTransferAUTH(uint256,address,address) (../sb/Wallet_F.sol#603-619)\n\t- Wallet.getBalance(address) (../sb/Wallet_F.sol#941-943)\n\t- Wallet.receive() (../sb/Wallet_F.sol#948-951)\n\t- Wallet.transfer(uint256,address) (../sb/Wallet_F.sol#493-501)\n\t- Wallet.transferAUTH(uint256,address,address) (../sb/Wallet_F.sol#581-595)\n\t- Wallet.withdrawn(uint256) (../sb/Wallet_F.sol#564-573)\n\t- Wallet.withdrawnAUTH(address,uint256) (../sb/Wallet_F.sol#673-689)\n\t- balances[owner] += fee (../sb/Wallet_F.sol#544)\n\tWallet.balances (../sb/Wallet_F.sol#431) can be used in cross function reentrancies:\n\t- Wallet.deposit() (../sb/Wallet_F.sol#482-486)\n\t- Wallet.exchange(string,address,uint256) (../sb/Wallet_F.sol#526-558)\n\t- Wallet.exchangeAUTH(string,address,address,uint256) (../sb/Wallet_F.sol#628-666)\n\t- Wallet.externalTransfer(uint256,address) (../sb/Wallet_F.sol#508-518)\n\t- Wallet.externalTransferAUTH(uint256,address,address) (../sb/Wallet_F.sol#603-619)\n\t- Wallet.getBalance(address) (../sb/Wallet_F.sol#941-943)\n\t- Wallet.receive() (../sb/Wallet_F.sol#948-951)\n\t- Wallet.transfer(uint256,address) (../sb/Wallet_F.sol#493-501)\n\t- Wallet.transferAUTH(uint256,address,address) (../sb/Wallet_F.sol#581-595)\